---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description="About The Forensic Brief — Post-Incident Analysis of AI Failure.">
  <article class="article-body prose-section">
    <header class="article-header">
      <span class="eyebrow">About</span>
      <h1 class="article-title">About The Forensic Brief</h1>
    </header>

    <div class="prose-body">
      <p>
        The Forensic Brief is an independent publication dedicated to the systematic, evidence-based analysis of AI failures. It publishes post-incident analyses, long-form essays on AI governance and accountability, and reusable templates for practitioners working with high-stakes AI systems.
      </p>

      <p>
        The publication is founded on the principle that understanding failure is essential to building reliable AI. Each incident is documented with structured timelines, root cause analysis, and contributory factor mapping — the same rigor applied to aviation safety investigations and medical device recalls.
      </p>

      <p>
        The Forensic Brief is not a news site. It does not cover AI product launches, funding rounds, or benchmark leaderboards. It covers what happens when AI systems fail in production — and what organizations can learn from those failures.
      </p>

      <h2>Author</h2>

      <p>
        Dr. Anandkumar Prakasam is the author and editor of The Forensic Brief. The publication represents independent research and analysis; it is not affiliated with any AI vendor, consulting firm, or advocacy organization.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>

      <p>
        For inquiries, corrections, or to report an AI incident for analysis, contact the author through the publication's official channels.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .article-header {
    margin-bottom: 48px;
  }

  .article-title {
    font-size: var(--text-3xl);
    margin: 12px 0 16px;
  }

  .prose-body {
    max-width: 620px;
    font-size: 0.92rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    line-height: 1.8;
  }

  .prose-body p + p {
    margin-top: 16px;
  }

  .prose-body h2 {
    margin-top: 32px;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
  }
</style>
